javelin.model.world.place.dungeon

Class Dungeon

  • java.lang.Object
    • javelin.model.world.WorldActor
      • javelin.model.world.place.WorldPlace
        • javelin.model.world.place.dungeon.Dungeon
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class Dungeon
extends WorldPlace
    A dungeon is an underground area of the world where the combats are harder but have extra treasure laying around. The in-game logic for dungeons is that they are a hideout of bandits, which is why they are sacrificeable by Incursions and are removed the game after a Squad leaves one (in this case it's assumed the bandits packed their stuff and left).

    alex

      • ENCOUNTERRATIO

        public static final double ENCOUNTERRATIO
        Assumes you will explore all the dungeon, being able to rest at the fountain mid-way for a total of 8 moderate encounters. This ignores the returning path towards the exit and getting to and from the dungeon itself, which means squads are supposed to be well equipped before diving in.
